@startuml basic_acceptance_test_class_diagram

title Method Call SCTF Test

package "Test Interface Definition" {
    class "TestMethodInterface<T>" as TestMethodInterface {
        + Method<int32(int32, int32)> add_numbers
        --
        + TestMethodInterface(T::Base&)
    }

    note right of TestMethodInterface
      T is either ProxyTrait or SkeletonTrait

      Instantiated as:
      - TestMethodProxy = AsProxy<TestMethodInterface>
      - TestMethodSkeleton = AsSkeleton<TestMethodInterface>

      Method<Signature> resolves to:
      - ProxyMethod<Signature> for proxy
      - SkeletonMethod<Signature> for skeleton
    end note
}

package "Provider Process" {
    class MethodProvider {
        + CreateAndOfferSkeleton() : Result<TestMethodSkeleton>
        - RegisterMethodHandlers(TestMethodSkeleton&) : void
    }

    class "TestMethodSkeleton" as Skeleton <<typedef>> {
        + SkeletonMethod<int32(int32, int32)> add_numbers
        --
        + OfferService() : ResultBlank
    }

    class "add_numbers_handler" as AddHandler <<lambda>> {
        + operator()(int32 a, int32 b) : int32
    }

    note bottom of AddHandler
      Lambda: [](int32 a, int32 b) { return a + b; }
    end note

    MethodProvider "1" o-- "1" Skeleton : creates & offers
    Skeleton "1" o-- "1" AddHandler : registers via add_numbers.Register()
}

package "Consumer Process" {
    class MethodConsumer {
        + CreateProxy() : Result<TestMethodProxy>
        + RunTests(TestMethodProxy&) : int
    }

    class "TestMethodProxy" as Proxy <<typedef>> {
        + ProxyMethod<int32(int32, int32)> add_numbers
        --
        {static} + FindService(InstanceSpecifier) : Result<ServiceHandleContainer>
    }

    note bottom of MethodConsumer
      Runs 2 tests:

      Test 1 (Copy):
        result = proxy.add_numbers(42, 17)
        verify: *result == 59

      Test 2 (Zero-Copy):
        [arg1, arg2] = proxy.add_numbers.Allocate()
        *arg1 = 42; *arg2 = 17
        result = proxy.add_numbers(move(arg1), move(arg2))
        verify: *result == 59
    end note

    MethodConsumer "1" o-- "1" Proxy : creates
    MethodConsumer ..> Proxy : calls add_numbers() in 2 ways
}

package "Method Classes Under Test" {
    class "SkeletonMethod<int32(int32, int32)>" as SkeletonMethod {
        + Register<Callable>(Callable&&) : ResultBlank
    }

    class "ProxyMethod<int32(int32, int32)>" as ProxyMethod {
        + Allocate() : Result<tuple<MethodInArgPtr<int32>, MethodInArgPtr<int32>>>
        + operator()(const int32&, const int32&) : Result<MethodReturnTypePtr<int32>>
        + operator()(MethodInArgPtr<int32>, MethodInArgPtr<int32>) : Result<MethodReturnTypePtr<int32>>
    }

    note right of SkeletonMethod
      Server-side method
      Stores user handler via Register()
      Invokes handler when call arrives via binding
    end note

    note right of ProxyMethod
      Client-side method
      Two call variants tested:
      1. Copy: operator()(const T&, const T&)
      2. Zero-copy: Allocate() + operator()(MethodInArgPtr, MethodInArgPtr)
    end note
}

Skeleton "1" *-- "1" SkeletonMethod : contains add_numbers
Proxy "1" *-- "1" ProxyMethod : contains add_numbers

TestMethodInterface <|.. Skeleton : instantiates
TestMethodInterface <|.. Proxy : instantiates

note as TestFlow
  **Test Flow:**

  1. Provider creates TestMethodSkeleton
  2. Provider registers lambda handler via add_numbers.Register()
  3. Provider offers service
  4. Consumer finds service
  5. Consumer creates TestMethodProxy
  6. **Test 1 - Copy Call:**
     Consumer: result = proxy.add_numbers(42, 17)
     Provider: handler invoked, returns 59
     Consumer: validates *result == 59
  7. **Test 2 - Zero-Copy Call:**
     Consumer: [arg1, arg2] = proxy.add_numbers.Allocate()
     Consumer: *arg1 = 42; *arg2 = 17
     Consumer: result = proxy.add_numbers(move(arg1), move(arg2))
     Provider: handler invoked, returns 59
     Consumer: validates *result == 59
end note

@enduml
